The paper discusses the Church-Turing thesis and its original definition in terms of classical algorithms. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category. However, the paper also mentions the evolution of the notion of algorithm and the introduction of new species of algorithms, which could make it relevant to the Computational Complexity (cs.CC), Programming Languages (cs.PL), Information Theory (cs.IT), and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-categories.
